caption: Expected a better experience with the food and the atmosphere.  Won't be back. The reviews that I read made me want to try it, I'm glad I didn't go for date night.
We love going to this perfectly situated restaurant in Downtown Frederick.  Flavor filled classic dishes, yummy drinks & indulgent desserts all in a beautiful presentation.

The cocktails here are so fresh, creative, and delicious. Came with a party of 7 and all of our food was stellar. Can’t say enough good things about our waitress, Marley. She was super attentive, upbeat, gave great recommendations, and made sure we were always fully stocked with water and drinks. She was one of the best waitresses I’ve ever had and really made the experience a great one! We sat outside for brunch and enjoyed every bit of it. Highly recommend!
Phenomenal scallops & steak!!
This place is level 10! The drinks are absolutely amazing 🤩 thank you bartenders! They couldn’t do it without you.

Just the most fanatic night in a long time, is how I would explain my recent birthday celebration with my daughter. Everything was perfect, from the SERVICE to the delicious meals. We had panko shrimp to start, along with their own blood orange martini (delish!), followed by lamb and  fillet minion (it was huge!), and then topped off with dessert: molten butter cake & Creme Brule- both heavenly!! You cannot go wrong!
Very elegant and convenient place. They serve generous meals and for fair rates. We enjoyed the food a lot and the staff were super personal and informative. Recommended.
I love this place!  Can't wait to go again!!
Great food & cocktails
The food and drinks were all incredible. The atmosphere was fantastic. Service was impeccable! This was our first time here and we can’t wait to go back!
Delicious food and drinks and even more amazing service! Our experience was great and our server Amanda was 100% the best!  Highly recommend!

Do not waste your money on this place. The food was horrible. The only thing good about it is their beer. It takes forever to get served, they take plates away from you before you are even done eating and they rush you out. Plus, it's very loud in their. My husband and I eat out a lot, so believe me. If you want to eat at a pricey place, skip this place. I'll try to attach a photo of the rockfish I had.

Stopped in while I was visiting Frederick. My waitress was knowledgable and friendly. She helped me pick out a bottle to my liking (drinking expensive wine is a bit new to me). The food was excellent. My mouth waters just thinking about my steak. The decor and over all style of the place was immaculate. Excellent atmosphere. I’ll gladly stop in next time I’m in Frederick. I highly suggest this place.
Awesome food great service definitely try the octopus app

The food was very delicious and the server was great. The freshness of the food was top level as I was wanting more. It was in a great location and I feel you must reserve before you come here because that's what I did. Overall I had a wonderful time here and come back again. I do recommend people to come try this place out if you are looking for some well-deserved food.
The Tasting Room!!! If you’re in the Frederick area, you can not leave without coming to this place.  The food and service here is nothing short of phenomenal!
(Translated by Google) Delicious food  (Original) Comida deliciosa
My wife and I always get the fillet and crab cakes and split them. It’s the perfect size meal for us, and the food is always delicious. We will be back soon
Great place for cocktails and desert.
Awesome ambiance, Great food, attention to details and accomodations were top notch! Jeff and awesome server
Food is always interesting, seasonal and well prepared. Atmosphere is pleasant, waitstaff accommodating, looking forward to eating here again soon.
Loved it!  Server Marly was personable and efficient.  Ordered a bunch of appetizers.  The standouts were the octopus and the lobster chowder.  Highly recommend.
One of the best restaurants in Frederick
Lovely experience! Food is delish, cocktails are amazing, service is top notch! Looking forward to going back.
Food and service was awesome Great experience. We definetely recomend this restaurant.
Served raw burger.  They took the raw burger that was cut in half and recooked it and reassembled it for me even with this pandemic going on. Be careful.
Awesome restaurant! The seasonal cocktails, delicious entrees, and great atmosphere made for a fun night!

This was our first visit (celebrating our wedding anniversary) and we will be back. The panko shrimp were good (and I am not a shrimp person), the blood orange cosmo was the best cosmo I've ever had. Husband had the filet and I had the beef short rib... all amazing. Oh, and the house salad dressing is out if this world.  Our server, Cynthia, was perfect. We felt like we were her only table.

The worst restaurant ever! someone told me that they was paying them $200 dollars for 40 hours that’s embarrassing!!!! Don’t work here also I got a cheeseburger from here it was disgusting the meat was to fat like no the fries felt like they wasn’t cooked right
Wine flights were GREAT. Apps, Entre's, Desert and Coffee were everything I was expecting.  See you again soon.

Local Gem set in picturesque downtown Frederick, MD this elegant restaurant serves up some of the best dishes with the freshest ingredients. The food is delicious, and the staff is about as Professional as the come. The Restaurant is also exceptionally clean. I highly recommend this amazing restaurant. We already can’t wait to come back!
The food is delicious and the service was outstanding. Worth every penny we spent.
excellent place with great food. everything is good, but FILET MIGNON is really really good.
Loved the service. There was a new waitress and she was excellent. The food was delicious and i had a great time dining in.

The food is consistently outstanding here. One of my favorite places to eat in downtown Frederick. They have excellent cocktails and a 5 star wine menu. The staff is well trained and friendly. A great place for a date night or Sunday brunch.
Stellar service, great ambience and out of this world food! Everything on the menu is amazing. Just order anything and whalla... Elation.
Had an amazing time last night at the tasting room. Food and service was impeccable. Highly recommend
Good quality food, pricey
Very delicious food and great options. Great atmosphere.
Great service and delish food!
Good food. Good drinks. Hospitable staff! 👌🏾
Service was A++++++, food and atmosphere spot on. Highly recommend lobster chowder,lobster ravioli anddddd the filet!!
Superb food (kudos to the chef)  and exceptionally friendly, attentive staff. A+ experience in the heart of beautiful downtown Frederick!

By far, the best dining experience my wife and I have had since moving to the DMV region! Great ambiance, service, and AMAZING food! We had: Braised octopus and Vichyssoise as a starter, Sea Scallops and the lamb as our entree, and creme-brûlée for dessert. Well, starting with the Octopus: perfectly soft, tender and juicy, seasoned to its perfection; Vichyssoise: creamy, DELICIOUS and arrived at the perfect eating temperature! Each entree came with a little salad (you can choose between house and Caesar salad). The lamb was so tender and delicious! The Sea Scallops were almost like butter, amazing texture and seasoned perfectly! The creme brûlée was perfectly sweet with no egg smell or taste! Jason, our server, suggested a great wine to go with the scallops and was very friendly. Overall, an excellent dining experience!!!
Amazing, as always! Fantastic food, great service and plenty to drink!
Great food!   Everything from the bread to the Short Ribs and Veal chop was amazing!   Hat is off to Tom (waiter) who made the evening superb.
Always an interesting menu at the Tasting Room, food is beautifully presented and service is very good.

Great food, service and atmosphere. If I had to nit-pick a criticism, I ordered Medium-Rare Filet Mignon, and it came out more Medium-Well, but it was such a perfect cut, and prepared beautifully that I didn't even complain because it was still delicious and tender.
An exceptional find!! Brilliant menu deliciously delivered. 5 Stars - yup!!
Dinner was excellent, service was fantastic.
Wonderful food, great service

I adore this place! They offer splendid food, their menu is decent, The chef in that spot is well trained, I love very much trying all their food. The dishes are always fresh, the attitude towards the clients  is nice. I  go often to this place and I not even once was disappointed.  I highly recommend it.

We had the stuffed calamari.  It tasted like the meat was from chef boyardee meat. Not good at all. The fried green tomatoes were just ok. Wait staff brings the utensils unwrapped and by hand no gloves. Inwas shocked in the age of COVID.  The lamb was delish.
All around top notch restaurant.  Fun, creative & diverse menu; fantastic wine & cocktail list; perfect atmosphere; top-tier service.  If you have not been, you absolutely must go.
The food was great. A very extensive wine list
My favorite restaurant in Frederick- always a great menu and consistently great customer service. They serve a great brunch on weekends - highly recommended!
Great staff, great food, and prompt food service. It was definitely a great place for a first anniversary dinner.

Top to bottom an exceptional experience. Drinks were amazing. Portions were perfect allowing us to enjoy 4 courses of delicious food without feeling overwhelmed. Would definitely recommend to anyone who is a foodie looking to enjoy a wonderful meal.

Had a good time with a party of 6. Food was great, and everything came out as ordered. I wish the service was faster, but it was busy for a Tuesday, which is a good sign. We tried a lot of different food, and the scallops were fantastic. Brussel sprouts weren't really roasted like we were hoping, but it happens. I definitely will be back!  The cocktails were fantastic! All around I recommend it to all my friends. Great atmosphere and vibe.

Delicious food with a very comfortable outdoor dining experience. Stand outs include: fried green tomatoes, beef carpaccio & crab ravioli. Also not to be missed: strawberry basil mimosa & the painkiller cocktail. Our waiter Stan was also fantastic.
The best filet in town... Great service
Had a wonderful experience. I asked for a sazerac and our bartender Sydney immediately gave me the best I’ve ever had. The food was delicious and it was a really great experience.

Good food, but slightly overpriced. The interior is very clean and well maintained to give an upscale appearance. The staff were very polite and professional. Wait staff checked in with us at the perfect frequency. Our glasses were never empty.

We are vacationing in the area and happened on a review of this fine restaurant. We're so glad we did. We enjoyed it so much we returned for lunch two days later. My GF had a Chicken Salad plate and I had the Burger - both were delicious. The second lunch I had the best Fish and Chips I have ever experienced. Light beer batter, almost tempura light with the fish very light and tasty. We are going back today for our third lunch in a week. Five stars for sure!
💓great food, amazing staff

My husband and I had been wanting to try TR for awhile and we decided to today. The service was amazing and so was the food! The manager was super nice and took a few minutes to talk with my husband and I before our meals were brought out. We will definitely be coming back in February for our wedding anniversary.
Amazing !

Fantastic food! I've lived in Frederick for 4 years and always passed TR without being inspired by their menu. I guess they're under new ownership and  have a new head chef. Menu and wine list are easily best in Frederick now, no contest. Matt is an incredible waiter, who can anticipate your needs and recommend fantastic food. The veal will definitely have me coming back!
Best service in Frederick, most delicious Caesar salad I've ever eaten, wine list is insane.
Excellent, as always. Great meal and service experience.
Absolutely delicious. Enjoyed my meal.

First time at The Tasting Room, Frederick MD Was exquisite, succulent food a la carte tasting  and amazing service experience. At door we received an warm welcoming from (Samantha), and at the table attentive and professional service from (Ricky). We party of two and we start sharing fresh Jumbo Crab Cake with hash brown, asparagus and tartar sauce, we smelling the Ocean from the freshest of the Crab, it was delicious. We also sharing Fettuccine with Main Lobster flavored with bacon lardon and combine with Wild Mushrooms...great touch in this plate, to be homemade pasta the pasta texture was perfectly cooked and well flavored. For Main Course we order Filet Mignon medium, tasting tender and juices  and well cooked, with side of  excellent potato au gratin and sauce bernaise,  we also shared braised short ribs... with baby carrots and crispy potato crumb, all good, and the food was cooked exactly the way should be, we enjoyed the food very much and we will return with family and friends.
Great spot. They know their wine and they do a great job with their menu too.
Great dining experience; the shrimp and grits were so delicious. The entire experience was very good.
Lobster mashed potatoes & steak melt in your mouth

Food is always good however the wait staff should realize that patrons who generously tip and are polite deserve a little more than condescension with zero appreciation. Not even a thank you and enjoy. Becoming like another Pistarro's Pizza. That staff is insufferable so stopped spending money there. Not surprising, that attitude is typical of many young people that feel we are doing them a favor by visiting the establishment. Get well soon.
Delicious, healthy food, a good drink selection and reasonable prices. Super friendly staff too.
One of our absolute favorites! Everything they do is perfect :)
The place offers an awesome variety of fresh food. I like eating here. Staff members are always very friendly, prices are affordable and the spot is always neat.

We met with friends at this restaurant for dinner. This restaurant was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, we were not disappointed. The staff members were very polite and we had an excellent feeling. The meal was great. We loved this place very much and we shall definitely come back again. We recommend this place to all.
Wonderful atmosphere. Excellent service. Delicious food.

Very intimate setting, excellent service and fantastic food. It is just too close of quarters for me. The server has limited room to stand by the tables and my elbows were pretty close to my neighbor....who wasn't seated at my table.
Great food but little over priced ..... we ordered few cocktails and entre....good service
One of the most incredible steaks I’ve ever eaten. Scalloped potatoes to boot. A must-visit in Frederick.
Food was excellent as always!
Great steaks and scallops. Went here for Galentine’s Day and had a great time!
This restaurant is smaller than expected. The food and service were good.

everything in their menu is tasty my favorite NEW YORK STRIP* creek stone farms | au gratin potatoes | mini salad | sauce béarnaise (seasonal mushrooms ) and LOBSTER WHIPPED POTATOES "TR CLASSIC" maine lobster | chive butter | sea salt.

While looking for quick bite in Frederick, almost everything was packed. They managed to fit us in as walk-ins at the last moment. Oh man, the food was excellent! Very nice atmosphere, and I would definitely think of this place when trying to decided on a restaurant for a date. Portions were good, taste was great. Our server was very friendly and we had an excellent time.
Great food and service!!
Great food and drinks just wish they had the chicken and waffles available.
Great food and service
Great ambience and great food.
The food here is always delicious, but their cocktails really stand out. Try the barrel aged Manhattan, or the Bunny Lebowski.
Great food and comfortable atmosphere

This place is delicious....we have been here a few times and always great.  Their crab dip is excellent ...you can taste the crab and Sherry. Delicious.  The chiliquilas were excellent. Great wine selection.  Food prices are reasonable. Definitely recommend.
Steak was great but really expensive
Wonderful Sunday Brunch!  The homemade sticky bun was incredible.  Service was excellent.  Even the coffee was great.  I will be back!
Outstanding fine dining. Spanish shrimp app. Duck was amazing. Filet mignon their specialty. Super service.
Nice place, awesome cocktails. Food was very good. Dessert? Look for the Huntsman 👍🏼
Delicious crab cakes and beautiful atmosphere.
Great service and good food

Very good service as always. Vinnie was great. The crabcakes were scorched on the bottom unfortunately. Taste was good but not how it was a few years ago. I believe the kitchen staff changed and it hasn't been the same since. Crabcakes used to be the best I have EVER tasted!!!!!!

Fantastic cuisine with an extensive wine menu. We had the rack of lamb and filet mignon. Both were cooked to perfection with excellent sides and unparalleled sauces. Staff is attentive and experienced. The decor is modern without being intimidating. Overall a fantastic experience. Highly recommend
Great bar, willing to make items not on current menu. Five stars always.

The menu is nice but definitely not healthy so don't go here expecting a low calorie meal. Their salad portions are very small and not a meal. Another option for vegetarians besides risotto would be great. They are accommodating to create sauteed veggies for a vegan but really was expecting something more creative from the tasting room for all types of diets. All the non veg options seemed delicious for my party. Drinks are excellent and service is impeccable. As someone who tries to combat my genetics by being healthy we will not be frequent visitors. I'm disappointed.
Had a great preholiday meal here for lunch. Everything was supurb. Had two small plates. Get a paloma!
We spent Christmas Eve at The Tasting Room and had a wonderful time. The crab cakes were outstanding and the service was outstanding.
It's nice but i prefer Clyde's
The tall, tattooed bartender is amazing. Super knowledgeable, friendly, and fast! If you want an awesome cocktail, come here!
Excellent food and  service
Great food and service!
absolutely delicious!
Great food and service.
Love it.  I know the owner his restaurants are great.  We're regulars here.  Best steaks in Frederick.
Beautiful restaurant, great service, the food was excellent and the individual unisex bathrooms were very clean
Nice place

This is the place to go when visiting Frederick.  Both the staff and selection far surpass any other restaurant/bar in downtown.  If you enjoy a low key ambiance, knowledgeable bartenders, and a sophisticated experience to your evening this is your final destination.

This is my husband and I's favorite restaurant in all of Frederick - it is our go-to restaurant for Anniversary's and Birthday dinners. The filet mignon is to die for, and we never leave hungry! Portions are very good size, so you definitely get the most for your money. Service is always amazing!

This is definitely a MUST HAVE brunch. Clean, charming and modern atmosphere with the most palate pleasing menu. There was not one item that was not perfectly prepared. I will definitely be making another reservation in the near future.
Best burger in town!
Food was excellent.   I was part of a group of 14 and our service was outstanding.
Outstanding food. Somewhat expensive.
Great food. Great service!

Been here twice, always a great experience.  My only complaint is the small plate menu during lunch isn't very intriguing to my wife and I.  We got the shrimp and grits and the salmon large plate lunches and it was all great.  The desserts were just as good.  I'd go back.  A gem in our small City.

*ALLERGY REVIEW* They did not take my allergy seriously and overall the service was disappointing. Here's my experience:  After telling the waiter about my allergy and then repeating when I placed my orders, the appetizer came out contaminated. The salad he was unsure of and had to verify, and though the allergen was not present, it was still concerning that he had to check after bringing it out to me. We had discussed how to modify the entre to accommodate my allergy, but the normal meal was brought out and I then waited more then 5 minutes for the waiter to return.  Meanwhile, my husband's dinner got cold and they did not take his back to keep warm as we asked. We had asked to have wine served with our meal and had to remind the waiter the second time my meal was brought out that we had asked for the wine. Up to this point the manager had been walking around to other tables and we thought he was unaware of our situation, but when he made it to our table he made a comment about my meal now being correct and moved on. At no point was an apology made by the manager and no discount was offered on our final bill. We were traveling from Boston to visit for my birthday and had been looking forward to trying this restaurant. Although the food was delicious, we were very disappointed by this experience.
Kitchen VERY slow. Waited over an hour to get our food and the place was only half full of patrons. Food pretty good but won’t go back.
Food & service good despite our order being wrong.
Always great service and great food.

The Tasting Room is a culinary gem in Frederick, Maryland. Some things, like their drinks menu and their main dishes, rotate seasonally. But their steaks, lobster chowder, and crab cakes--all TR traditional dishes, never go out of style. And, the carrot cake with cream cheese icing is a great way to finish. You will love the service, the atmosphere, and the food.
From the hostess to the waiter, service was excellent. Shrimp appetizer was very good. Fillet is the best in Frederick by far. You owe it to yourself to dine at this restaurant

I have been a Frederick native for quite some time. Places come...places go...but this is by far my favorite place to go in Frederick for fine food and drinks. The staff is beyond amazing. I will forever be loyal.
Food is well prepared.   Definitely need reservations because it is a small restaurant
Amazing food and outstanding service. I almost always come here when I'm in the area- the sushi tuna appetizer and gazpacho are second to none.
Really great meal,  great service, great wine/cocktails
Excellent food. All the staff were super friendly.

Very pleased, as usual. We went last night, and it took an abnormal amount of time for our food to come out. They handled it extremely well, we were very pleased and the food was definitely worth the wait.
Lots of good food! I like the small plates!
Lovely place, but service was a little off. Had to ask for spoons for our soup if I had to be honest. But dont let that stop you...the soup and everything else was amazingly good.
Absolutely assume!
Salmon cakes are to die for.  Great ambiance in great service.
Wonderful meal with a pretty amazing guy.
One of the best dinners we've had in a long time! Not cheap, but worth it. The lobster chowder and creme brulee were some of the best I've ever had...and that's saying a lot!!!
Great lunch today!

The staff is knowledgeable about the food and beverages offered. I enjoy the ambience especially when here for dinner. The lobster chowder is amazing...only wish it was a larger portion :) I haven't had a bad experience or meal here to date. They also give birthday dessert - I had chocolate sorbet with berries!
Very good location, food and drinks.  Can be a fun cocktail hour, they make the best martinis!
It was nice good service and the food was delicious I took my wife there for her birthday
Great experience, great customer service, clean and tidy! Thank you for hospitality.
Great classy place with fantastic food. Try the calamari it's heaven. ❤️
Tasty spanish shrimp
Always awesome....never a bad experience
Great atmosphere, and loved the food. Will be back👍🏽
Great service, very good food and an imaginative wine selection.
Atmosphere and Food - off the chart
Superb food.

Went last night for my dad's birthday. My favorite restaurant in Frederick. They filet Oscar was amazing and they brought out some great birthday sorbet for my dad and we ordered the carrot cake as well, all made in house!  Our server Matt was awesome. We all agreed he made the night that much better with his interactions and great service. Can't wait to go back!
They have high quality food and delicious signature cocktails. There are no wrong options. All around great experience! It's definitely pricey but it's worth it

My 10 year old granddaughter wanted her birthday party at this restaurant. My family and I had dined at this establishment in pass in and always that received and peccable service. But this time we received subpar service and the manager was no help. Our party was accused of stealing food from the restaurant because of our colors.  If it was not for my granddaughter who was in intendents we probably would have insisted on a more respectful behavior from the staff and the manager. Based on this I can no longer recommend this restaurant for any occasion unless the management and the staff is trained on culture sensitivities and bias training.
Always a good meal, attentive service and a be seen atmosphere.   One of our top three Frederick restaurants.
Very good food as well as service. Expect to pay $100+ if you have a couple of drinks with your meal. My wife and i had an appetizer as well as desert with our entree'.
Good service and clean place. Fancy look.
Top notch, excellent service and food
Excellent food and drinks. It is a little pricey.

Server was 5 stars Good 5 stars Very clean 5 stars The drinks kept coming and the food was  brought out at the perfect time 5 stars on that. If you love good food and great service this is a must stop. So far best restaurant in Frederick.
Food was awesome

Food was good not great.  Serve did ok with the serving aspect but when it came time for the bill you was somehow unable to split the bill. 1 vodka tonic and a rock fish special cost me over $100....not cool!
Very good food, awesome atmosphere... great for a date night.
The food we got from this place was great and lots of variety to choose from.The staff were friendly and efficient. Would highly recommend.
First time here and I can’t say enough great things about this place 👌I’ve been in the business for 40 years my compliments to the chef and waiting staff 👌 you’re treating like a king 👑
This was our favorite restaurant when we lived in Frederick. The food was consistently good, and service was always top notch. Best Caesar salad and lobster bisque I’ve ever had. Highly recommend.
Amazing cocktails!!! Food is top notch!! Try the scallops to DIE for!!! Yummmmm!!!
Absolutely fantastic dining experience. Service was superb and friendly
Great meal with friends. Server was friendly and attentive
Great place.  Food is always exceptional.  Dave the General Manager will make sure all is perfect for your visit!  Highly recommended!  PS. Try the Filet if there for dinner!
Pricey, interesting offerings but we missed most because they were out.
A nice stop for happy hour with interesting drinks and good prices
The food was amazing as always except the staff could be more prepared with knowledge on the wine selection. Food was fast and delicious though so I can't complain too much. Great Filet!
The place is small and it can get a bit noisy, but the food is excellent and the service is always great!
Wonderful wine selection.  Great food.
Great meal again!  Nicely prepared, good service, fantastic overall.  One of our favorite restaurants!
Amazing food and wine selection. Sever was very attentive and a pleaser. Love the dinner time atmosphere. Definetily coming back for another romantic and elegant evening.
Delicious food crabcakes, crab dip, lobster bisque!! Enjoyed eating here wil definitely recommend this place.
It's pricey and the servings are small, but the food is delicious. Service was perfect.
Fantastic brunch.  Chicken and waffles cooked to perfection.  Moist chicken with perfect coating... Savory, crunchy, light sweetness.  Light and fluffy sticky buns.

Somewhat disappointing in presentation of meals. The monkfish and mashed potatoes with pieces of lobster was recommended.  The presentation was unattractive, lacking in color.  The mashed potatoes were served in a martini glass.  They cooled down quickly. Generally uninspiring.  Not much taste in the monkfish though the sauce helped.  The duck was overcooked and was sent back.  Prepared well on next attempt.

Was very expensive. Great place for a one time visit. Service was great. Food to cash ratio was off. As in every upscale establishment but there are better places to visit. I.E Hooch and Banter fyi. Not as fancy in side but nonetheless superior.

Stopped in The Tasting Room last minute after flying into Frederick Airport. We were able to get a table last minute without issue via open table. This was our first visit and it probably won’t be our last. Our eyes were bigger than our stomachs so we took home a bit of food after ordering several appetizers to share AND entrees.  The portion sizes were much larger than we expected. My favorite item had to be the cauliflower soup. I was a little surprised at how basic it looked when it arrived at the table. Cauliflower, broth, some vegetables, and noodles. It was delicious and I’ve been craving it ever since.
Great Maduro Brown Ale, great burger!
Service is very slow.  Food not worth the prices
Excellent brunch on Sundays!!
Restaurant week, shared alot of apps. Looking forward to the fois gras but little overcooked. Rest of food great. Server new but did ok. No reso. But got seated immediately. Will be back.
Plenty of room... Lots of tasting.

I received a gift card to The Tasting Room 2 years ago and LOVED it.  Went back again and got the same exact thing and it tasted even better.  You will not be disappointed with this restaurant.  AMAZING!!!
Great food and atmosphere!
Clean place, friendly staff, and great food!

Nice menu except that THREE of the items I ordered were unavailable so I  guess the menu is theoretically nice. Went for Sunday brunch and there were no specialty coffees because the machine was broken. So no cappuccino.  So I  ordered the hot buttered rum, but no that wasn't available either. My first entree was not available supposedly because of Valentine's day, which was three days earlier.  So all of that aside. I had a very good meal there. We split an order of sticky buns which were delicious.  And I  had the shrimp and grits. The broth was fabulous.  Service was prompt.  The decor is nice but we sat next to a large window with a significant crack in it.

This was my first time to the tasting room. Superb!  That was delicious food good drink and prices to write home about. It is very expensive and I would say maybe a touch too expensive for what they offer but it wasn't the food that wasn't up to snuff. It was some of the service. Our waiter Tre was cool and very well groomed for that type of restaurant, however some of the busing staff need to be a little better versed at when people are done or not. They either cleared plates too early or way too late. I expect top quality for prices like that and it was lacking just a little. Overall it was great. Had a good time with fam. Would go again. I got the fioe gras and the monkfish. Both were excellent and well worth it. Check it out if you get to market Street.

Overall a great experience.  Appetizers: 4/5, delicious, but skimpy. Got the cheese plate. Ambiance: 4/5, would vote 5, but we were sat near the restrooms Service: 4/5, solid, no complaints, but not mind blowing. Dessert: 5/5, delicious, also a little skimpy, but the taste made up for the small portion. Had the chocolate mousse cake. Entree:5/5, saved the best for last. This took the overall experience from a solid 4-4.5 to a 5. Their steaks are out of this world good. Great portions, incredible flavor and perfectly cooked. Would go back here just to have another steak.  Meal was around $150 for two people. 1 app, 2 entrees, 1 dessert and no drinks.
Stark, uninviting atmosphere in which you consume expensive small portions.
Went for Valentine's Day. Mood was nice. Tables are small. Some food had lots of flavor other was bland.
Great food and a great value. Jonathan was very patient with all my questions
Stopped in for the best esspresso Martini
This has to be one of the greatest restaurants in Frederick!  Get the filet!
The appetizers in the soup were excellent and I loved how they did not rush you through your meal
Great lunch. Good wines. Nice beer selection. Tasty cheeseburger.

Nice service, nice place but fishes weren't good. I ordered roasted Monkfish, they served with truffled cuscus and it was so heavy. My husband ordered organic Salmon and it was better than mine but still not good.
It was my first time going there. Great food and great service.
Long history of serving the city of Frederick outstanding owners
Always a great menu.  Monkfish was phenomenal!
Had streak.  Wasn’t as good as wine kitchen.  Wife enjoyed her drinks and fish.

I liked the food, little pricy, but your getting quality, I thought the wait staff seemed preoccupied with something else, not as friendly as I am used to. But the food was delicious, very clean and tidy.
Excellent food. Cozy yet elegant atmosphere. Wait staff was efficient. Overall a nice experience.

Excellent place to have dinner or get a cocktail in Frederick. Multiple visits over the years always result in excellent experience in food, drinks, and a good time. Good service from Kendall and food from the chef, a real gem, worth the one hour drive! We started with two decadent choices, the lobster chowder and the fois grad. Excuse me while I get on my soap-box, what sets food apart in my opinion is technique and ingredients, the tasting room technique is simple and straight forward, but also precise. And the ingredients are so fresh and flavorful, they would only be better if they grew them ina tasting room farm. The fois gras was cooked perfectly, rare enough with a slight crisp on the surface, the super thin jam crostini was not an after thought but a perfect texture addition to the fatty duck; the chowder was creamy but not oily and the tender pieces of lobster and potato and onion and corn swam in the tastiest creamiest sauce. Mmm! The superiority of the ingredients was really showcased in the fois gras l, the honey, the fruits and the herbs were so fresh and full of flavor. For entree we had the fillet mignon and the crab dip. We upgraded the potato gratin to lobster creamed potatoes and were not disappointed. For dessert both the carrot cake and the crepe brûlée were on point. The only thing we were not happy with was the cauliflower stew but that was more of a palate than anything and they did not charge us for it. The tea selection from Mighty Leaf organic was the perfect ending to a lovely meal that was both refreshing and decadent.

The best restaurant in Frederick, frankly.  You will shell out a bit for it, but it is worth it.  I have been here a number of times and I have seldom been disappointed.  The food is excellent (including possibly the best burger in Frederick for lunch) and sophisticated; the drinks constitute a fine selection of wines and beers and the best cocktails in Frederick.  Additionally, their happy hour is a serious bargain.  And the service is generally good, a rarity (sadly) in this town.  I fully intend to make this a regular stop in my local restaurant patronage for the coming future.

First of all the food was really good, this review is solely based on customer service.  We came in with a 12 top last night. We had a reservation, we arrived on time, and the table was ready for us. Our waiter seemed a little Irritated to be serving us from the onset. When the entrees arrived my fiancé was in the restroom and our waiter sat down a plate of scallops in front of her seat. My fiancé does not enjoy any type of seafood so I said  that I think he had placed them in the wrong spot, someone else must have ordered scallops. He definitely heard me but chose to ignore me. I told him again that he misplaced the scallops and he cut me off mid sentence and forcefully told me she ordered the scallops. Then insued a childish, back and forth argument about whether she did or didn’t order scallops and I told him that she would never order seafood because she does not enjoy the taste.  The waiter told me I was wrong and he would have to check with my fiancé when she got back from the restrooms.  So she comes back a minute later and the waiter rudely shoves a menu in her face and asks her what she ordered. Keep in mind she has no idea we’ve just been arguing about scallops (yes, it was as ridiculous as it sounds)  so she is taken aback by his aggressiveness. Of course, she tells him she didn’t order scallops and they end up bringing out her actual order. He does not apologize, he just looks further annoyed. Not cool when he’s the one who took down the wrong order.  To be fair he may have been having a bad day, I hope that is not his typical attitude. Plus, the scallops did look pretty good.  All in all, the food was good and the server was the rudest I’ve ever had. For a fraction of the price you could be treated better at Waffle House.

I went here in a date with my wife this past week. I’ve lived in Frederick for 9 years and finally made it to this place. My wife went once before and loved it. My local friends said this was the place to go and to try the Fillet Mignon: rare to medium rare.  I did just that. My wife and I both ordered the mignon. We spent about $200 for two of us - without appetizers. So this is a once in awhile date for us.  I would like to see a better selection of craft beer.
